<subSubSection id="FBF16577FFFBFFC0FF7D2CADF064FA7B" pageId="12" pageNumber="301" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="B35436FCFFFBFFC0FF7D2CADF064FA7B" blockId="12.[151,760,947,1771]" pageId="12" pageNumber="301">
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFFBFFC0FF7D2CADF01DFC1B" bold="true" box="[151,268,947,971]" pageId="12" pageNumber="301">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Antennae brown. Antennomere II longer than III. Pronotum with smoky stripe not reaching posterior margin. Thoracic and abdominal pleurites and sternites with black spots (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFFBFFC0FEF42B0AF07EFBFB" box="[286,367,1044,1067]" captionStart="Figs 1" captionStartId="2.[151,188,2036,2055]" captionTargetBox="[239,1341,201,1954]" captionTargetId="figure-13@2.[179,1408,189,1996]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1A–F. Dorsal and ventral surface. A–B – Hypoxys amyoti sp. nov.; C–D – Hypoxys aspilogaster sp. nov.; E–F – Hypoxys belenensis sp. nov. Scale bars = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177529" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177529/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="301">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
). Anterior excavation of metasternal process harboring fourth, third and part of second rostral segment (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFFBFFC0FF142B4AF040FBBB" box="[254,337,1108,1131]" captionStart="Figs 8" captionStartId="11.[153,189,2032,2051]" captionTargetBox="[160,1432,1137,2008]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 8A–B.Hypoxys belenensis sp.nov.A – genital plates;B – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177543" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177543/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="301">Fig. 8B</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFFBFFC0FE8F2B4DF334FBBB" bold="true" box="[357,549,1107,1131]" pageId="12" pageNumber="301">
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFFBFFC0FE8F2B4DF30FFBBB" bold="true" box="[357,542,1107,1131]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="301">Female genitalia</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Genital plates (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFFBFFC0FD262B4AF1AAFB5B" captionStart="Figs 8" captionStartId="11.[153,189,2032,2051]" captionTargetBox="[160,1432,1137,2008]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 8A–B.Hypoxys belenensis sp.nov.A – genital plates;B – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177543" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177543/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="301">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
). Valvifers 8 posterior margin with posterolateral angles blunt, inner angles dentiform; both angles posteriorly directed to base of laterotergites 8; imaginary line tangent to posterolateral angles not reaching distal margin of valvifers 9; excavation widely U-shaped. Valvulae 8 well visible. Apices of laterotergites 8 clearly above level of apices of abdominal segment VII. Laterotergites 9 surpassing band connecting laterotergites 8; apices at level of imaginary line tangent to apices of abdominal segment VII. 
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFFBFFC0FD552A6DF1EFFA7B" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="301">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FBF16577FFFBFFC0FF5F2AAAF0FBF99B" pageId="12" pageNumber="301" type="description">
